---
description: Frontend UI edits stay visual-only; do not break API or backend contracts
globs: frontend/**/*
alwaysApply: false
---

# Design vs behavior (frontend)

When adjusting layout, styles, spacing, typography, or dimensions:

- Keep the same React state variable names, `onChange` handlers, and data passed to API clients (`hostApi`, etc.).
- Keep `HostProfile` / DTO field names and `handleSave` payload shape aligned with backend DTOs.
- Do not add validation (max length, pattern, stripping characters) unless product and backend explicitly require it. If you add a limit (e.g. postal code max length), use rules that still accept values the backend already stores (e.g. alphanumeric postal codes).
- Prefer CSS and presentational props only; avoid changing business logic for purely visual tickets.
